{"article_id":"gIHmXRnRWoJKgsX7","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Senate leaders explored the outlines of a deal Monday","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"that would end the two-week-old government shutdown","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"and give the Treasury Department enough borrowing room","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"to stave off a potential default this month ,","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"but all sides cautioned","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"that the specifics are all still up for negotiation .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"\" Everyone just needs to be patient , \"","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid , Nevada Democrat , told his colleagues on the chamber floor late Monday .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"\" Perhaps tomorrow will be a bright day .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"We ' re not there yet . \"","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"He and his Republican counterpart , Sen. Mitch McConnell of Kentucky , have settled on the basic pieces :","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"the government would be funded for several months ,","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"and President Obama would be given room","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"to raise the debt into next year ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"with the House and Senate appointing negotiators","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"to try to reach a broader budget deal in the meantime .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"But the exact dates of the debt and spending extensions , and the add-ons","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"- such as delays or restrictions on Obamacare -","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"are still all under negotiation ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"aides said .","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"And","depth":5},{"id":21,"text":"even if Mr. Reid and Mr. McConnell are able to strike a deal ,","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"it ' s unclear whether it could get through the GOP-controlled House ,","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"where conservatives said","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"the outlines sounded to them like a surrender .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"\" When you ' re giving 98 , 99 percent of Obamacare ,","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"I don ' t see how that would ever pass over here ,","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"if indeed it passes the Senate , \"","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"said Rep. Tim Huelskamp , Kansas Republican .","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":4},{"id":30,"text":"Next move on U.S. credit rating ?","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"' D ' for default","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"Still , the mere prospects of a deal","depth":5},{"id":33,"text":"that would give the government more room","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"to expand its $ 16.7 trillion debt","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"sent the stock markets higher Monday .","depth":4},{"id":36,"text":"Mr. Obama had asked the top party leaders to come to the White House for talks Monday afternoon","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"but canceled that meeting ,","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"it made more sense to give Mr. Reid and Mr. McConnell space","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"to work .","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"For his part , the president visited a local food bank , Martha ' s Table ,","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"where some furloughed federal workers were helping out .","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"Mr. Obama said","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"\" some progress \" had been made .","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"\" But we ' ll see","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"if the progress is real , \"","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"the president told reporters .","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"Mr. Obama said","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"some Senate Republicans recognize","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"\" it ' s not tenable ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"it ' s not smart ,","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"it ' s not good for the American people to let America default . \"","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"But the president added ,","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"\" If Republicans aren ' t willing to set aside their partisan concerns","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"in order to do what ' s right for the country ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"we stand a good chance","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"of defaulting ,","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"and defaulting could have a potentially have a devastating effect on our economy . \"","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"The Treasury Department has said","depth":5},{"id":60,"text":"it will run out of borrowing room Thursday ,","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"leaving it with only cash on hand","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"to pay bills .","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"That could last a couple of weeks ,","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"or it could be exhausted almost immediately ,","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"analysts said .","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"- How long a stopgap funding bill should run .","depth":4},{"id":67,"text":"Senate Republicans wanted a longer version","depth":6},{"id":68,"text":"that would push well into 2014 ,","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"which would have also locked in the beginning of the sequester spending cuts .","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"Democrats have balked ,","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"they still hope to undo those cuts","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"before they kick in on Jan. 15 .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"- How much borrowing authority to give the Treasury Department .","depth":5},{"id":75,"text":"Here , the order is reversed","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"and Republicans want a shorter extension ,","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"while Democrats want the longest time frame","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"they can get .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"Mr. Reid has proposed going to the end of 2014 ,","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"which would last beyond the next congressional elections .","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"- What dents will be made to Obamacare .","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"Possible items include stricter eligibility verification for those","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"who would get subsidies under the Affordable Care Act , and then a repeal of some taxes or fees .","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"Sen. Susan M. Collins , Maine Republican , had proposed delaying a tax on medical devices","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"- a move","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"that has bipartisan support .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"But Democratic leaders and the White House have resisted changes to Mr. Obama ' s Affordable Care Act ,","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"leaving Republicans to search for another concession on that subject ,","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"which is what started the conservative revolt against the spending resolution and debt ceiling in the first place .","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"\" I ' m baffled by the White House ' s opposition to a two-year delay in the tax , \"","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"Ms. Collins told CNN on Monday ,","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"that a bipartisan group of senators had found agreement on that item ,","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"and pointing to a nonbinding vote earlier this year","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"to repeal the tax ,","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"which garnered the support of 79 senators .","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"The White House has been insistent","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"that the government reopen","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"and the debt be raised","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"without any conditions ,","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"repeatedly comparing Republican demands on Obamacare to hostage-taking and terrorism .","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"House Republicans remain a major hurdle ,","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"and conservatives said","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"what they were hearing about the Senate deal was grim .","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"\" I think","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"we ' ll have a hard time with our conference , with a number of members ,","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"because of the lack of Obamacare features in that , \"","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"said Rep. Charles W. Boustany Jr. , Louisiana Republican .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"That opposition has party leaders in both houses talking strategy , such as which chamber should go first","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"and how many House Democrats would be needed","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"to pass the deal there .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":223,"left":147,"right":222,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":140,"right":146,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":131,"right":139,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":121,"right":130,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":117,"right":120,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":117,"left":115,"right":116,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":115,"left":0,"right":114,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":114,"left":1,"right":113,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":113,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":120,"left":118,"right":119,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":130,"left":126,"right":129,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":10,"right":125,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":11,"right":124,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":124,"left":122,"right":123,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":128,"right":19,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":127,"right":18,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":127,"left":16,"right":17,"relat